[## LECTURE 7.3 — PRE-MERGE VALIDATION: REQUIRED STATUS CHECKS]

33
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Reviews catch logic errors.
But what about code that passes review but fails tests?
Or introduces a vulnerability? Or breaks the build?

34
00:00:30,000 --> 00:01:00,000
You need automated validation that runs on every PR
and blocks merge if anything fails.
Required status checks are the answer.

35
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Let me walk through the complete pre-merge validation pipeline.

36
00:01:30,000 --> 00:02:00,000
First, secret scan with Gitleaks.
Checks for hardcoded secrets in the entire Git history.
Uses the dot gitleaks dot toml configuration.

37
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Second, Trivy filesystem scan.
Scans the codebase, Dockerfile, and configuration files.
Fails on CRITICAL and HIGH vulnerabilities.

38
00:02:30,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Third, dependency scan with pip-audit.
Scans pyproject dot toml for vulnerable Python packages.
Fails on CRITICAL and HIGH severity findings.

39
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Fourth, code quality with Ruff and MyPy.
Ruff checks linting and formatting.
MyPy performs static type checking with strict mode.

40
00:03:30,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Fifth, unit tests with coverage.
Runs all unit tests. Fails if coverage drops below sixty percent.
Outputs coverage XML for upload to Codecov.

41
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Sixth, Conftest validation for infrastructure changes.
Only runs if the PR has the infrastructure label.
Renders Helm templates and validates them against Rego policies.

42
00:04:30,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Seventh, migration test for database changes.
Only runs if the PR has the database label.
Starts a PostgreSQL test container.
Tests upgrade, downgrade, and re-upgrade.

43
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Now add these as required status checks in branch protection.
Update the branch protection configuration.
Add the context names to the required status checks list.

44
00:05:30,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Now every PR must pass all these checks before merge.
If any fails, the merge button is disabled.

45
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:30,000
What does a developer see when they forget to run tests?
Required checks pending. Unit tests pending. Integration tests pending.
And required checks failing. A secret scan failure or a type error.

46
00:06:30,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Merge is blocked until all checks pass.
Your lab exercise is to create a PR that intentionally breaks a test.
Verify the merge is blocked. Fix the test and verify the merge becomes available.

47
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:30,000
In the next lecture, we will deploy ArgoCD GitOps.
And enable self-heal to revert manual changes.


