[## LECTURE 7.4 — ARGOCD GITOPS: SELF-HEALING AND DRIFT DETECTION]

48
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:30,000
GitHub protects your code.
But what about your Kubernetes configuration?
Someone with kubectl access could change a deployment directly,
bypassing all your controls.

49
00:00:30,000 --> 00:01:00,000
That is configuration drift.
ArgoCD implements GitOps. Your cluster state is always synced to what is in Git.
If someone changes something directly, ArgoCD reverts it automatically.

50
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Create the ArgoCD application manifest.
Source repo URL is your GitHub repository.
Target revision is main. Path is infrastructure forward slash helm.

51
00:01:30,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Destination server is the Kubernetes API.
Namespace is financial-rag.
Sync policy automated. Prune true. Delete resources not in Git.

52
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Self-heal true. Revert any manual changes.
Allow empty false.
Sync options include CreateNamespace, ApplyOutOfSyncOnly, and PruneLast.

53
00:02:30,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Retry limit five. Backoff duration five seconds.
Factor two. Max duration three minutes.

54
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Apply the ArgoCD application.
Now let us see drift detection in action.
Check sync status. argocd app get financial-rag.
Sync Status should be Synced. Health Status Healthy.

55
00:03:30,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Now manually change a deployment.
kubectl scale deployment financial-rag-agent-api to ten replicas.
Wait thirty seconds. Check sync status again.
It will be OutOfSync.

56
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:30,000
View the drift. argocd app diff.
It shows the live replicas ten and the desired replicas six.
ArgoCD self-heals within seconds. The sync status returns to Synced.

57
00:04:30,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Integrate ArgoCD with GitHub Actions for automated sync after merges.
When you push to main, the deploy workflow runs.
Install ArgoCD CLI. Login to ArgoCD.

58
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Run argocd app sync. Wait for sync to complete.
Verify the health status is Healthy.
Save the deployment evidence to S3.

59
00:05:30,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Save ArgoCD sync history as evidence.
argocd app history financial-rag.
Save the sync status as JSON.

60
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Your lab exercise is to make a change to your Helm chart and push to Git.
Watch ArgoCD auto-sync.
Then manually change a resource in Kubernetes.
Watch ArgoCD revert it.

61
00:06:30,000 --> 00:07:00,000
In the next lecture, we will implement canary deployments.
And automated rollback on error rate spikes.


